</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName authority="Mohanasundaram, 1984" authorityName="Mohanasundaram" authorityYear="1984" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Ashieldophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ashieldophyes" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ashieldophyes</taxonomicName>
Mohanasundaram, 1984, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit, 2019" authorityName="Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Brevishieldophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brevishieldophyes" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brevishieldophyes</taxonomicName>
Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit, gen. n., and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit, 2019" authorityName="Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Mesoshieldophyes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesoshieldophyes" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesoshieldophyes</taxonomicName>
Chakrabarti &amp; Pandit, gen. n. belong to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Ashieldophyinae">Ashieldophyinae</taxonomicName>
of family 
<taxonomicName family="Eriophyidae" lsidName="" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="family">Eriophyidae</taxonomicName>
in having small or moderately developed shield, lacking opisthosomal setae d and e, coxae widely separated anteriorly, female genitalia appressed to the coxae and with a triangular cover flap. These three genera can easily be separated by the characters given in Table 1 and in the key provided below. The genus is monotypic.
</paragraph>
